CAPE TOWN - Energy and Mineral Resources Minister Gwede Mantshe said the mining industry will soon be able to generate their own electricity. "Self-generation will be part of our make-up of energy supply to take the pressure off from Eskom," he said. "Self-generation for own use will be allowed. All that is needed to be done is to register. READ: Mining companies seek permission to generate their own power "However, generation to sell is business. This would require licensing.” He was speaking at the 2020 Mining Indaba in Cape Town. Mining companies have approached Mantashe, asking the government to allow them to build their own power plants so they are not subject to an unreliable energy provider.